WEBVTT

00:01.268 --> 00:02.535
We don't want
any trouble.

00:02.603 --> 00:03.536
Hey, take it easy, man.
Just take it easy.

00:03.604 --> 00:04.603
[ Grunts ]

00:04.672 --> 00:05.938
Back, back!
Inside.

00:06.007 --> 00:07.472
[ Gunshots ]

00:07.542 --> 00:09.008
Manny: Hey! Colin!
[ Horn honking ]

00:09.076 --> 00:10.075
Janine: Colin?

00:10.077 --> 00:13.412
He's dead, Janine.
He's dead.

00:13.480 --> 00:14.547
How long
have you known

00:14.615 --> 00:16.949
that Adrian's
been talking to the feds?

00:17.018 --> 00:18.150
Handle it.

00:18.219 --> 00:19.752
Or I'll have to
turn it over to Pope.

00:19.820 --> 00:21.954
Listen to me. If you stay,
you will never be safe!

00:22.023 --> 00:23.556
I love you, too,
you know?

00:23.624 --> 00:26.225
But you're the worst thing
that ever happened to me.

00:26.293 --> 00:28.027
♪♪

00:28.095 --> 00:30.963
These people are Preppers,
paranoid.

00:31.032 --> 00:32.231
♪♪

00:32.299 --> 00:33.766
I have a job
for us.

00:33.834 --> 00:36.301
It's quick,
nothing fancy,

00:36.371 --> 00:37.370
big score.

00:37.438 --> 00:38.904
What is this place?

00:38.973 --> 00:40.639
Smurf: Your father's
buried here.

00:40.708 --> 00:42.575
Right in front
of that tree.

00:42.643 --> 00:43.842
This is
your Uncle Jed.

00:43.911 --> 00:46.779
And that's
your cousin, Odin.

00:46.847 --> 00:48.381
Jed!
[ Grunts ]

00:48.449 --> 00:51.384
Come out, boys,
let's do this!

00:51.452 --> 00:53.919
[ Gunshots ]

00:53.988 --> 00:54.853
Smurf!

00:54.922 --> 00:55.988
Shoot me, Andrew.

00:56.057 --> 00:57.856
No.
She's gonna do it,
Pope!

00:57.925 --> 00:59.725
Smurf! Christ!
She's gonna do it!

00:59.794 --> 01:02.261
Smurf! Christ!

01:02.329 --> 01:05.330
♪♪

01:05.400 --> 01:06.999
Those homeschool
Prepper freaks

01:07.068 --> 01:09.468
are gonna figure out
where we live.

01:09.536 --> 01:11.070
They gonna
come after us?

01:11.138 --> 01:12.839
Maybe.

01:13.408 --> 01:17.276
♪♪

01:17.344 --> 01:22.882
♪ She stares deeply

01:22.950 --> 01:26.952
♪ Locked inside me

01:26.954 --> 01:29.989
♪ Burnin' brightly

01:32.827 --> 01:38.697
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:38.766 --> 01:41.967
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin

01:42.036 --> 01:45.471
♪ Every night now, they'll win

01:48.976 --> 01:51.777
♪ Come and meet my black hole

01:51.779 --> 01:55.648
♪ Got a big black hole

01:55.716 --> 01:59.452
♪ Got a big black hole

01:59.520 --> 02:03.188
♪ I've got a big black hole

02:03.190 --> 02:07.392
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

02:07.394 --> 02:11.330
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

02:11.398 --> 02:13.398
♪ Got a

02:13.400 --> 02:23.408
♪♪

02:23.410 --> 02:29.548
♪♪

02:29.617 --> 02:32.485
Renn?

02:32.553 --> 02:35.488
Renn?

02:35.556 --> 02:37.089
Yo.

02:37.158 --> 02:38.157
Renn.

02:38.225 --> 02:39.825
Renn, hey.
Hey, you got to get up.

02:39.894 --> 02:40.960
Hey.
What?
I just got to sleep.

02:41.028 --> 02:41.961
Come on.
We gotta go.

02:42.029 --> 02:43.362
Shh, shh.
Get up.

02:43.430 --> 02:45.430
What's going on?

02:45.500 --> 02:47.432
Yo,
is this thing good to go?

02:47.502 --> 02:48.701
Yeah.
What's going on?

02:48.769 --> 02:50.836
There's been some blowback
from the last job.

02:50.905 --> 02:52.171
[ Sighs ] Smurf?
Yeah.

02:52.239 --> 02:53.572
What kind of blowback?

02:53.641 --> 02:55.440
Smurf knew the guy
that she ripped off.

02:55.510 --> 02:57.042
I guess
it was Pope's uncle.

02:57.111 --> 02:58.243
Hey.

02:58.313 --> 03:00.046
Talk to me.

03:02.850 --> 03:04.783
Pope and Smurf were gonna
distract the guy

03:04.852 --> 03:07.720
while we stole his shit.

03:07.788 --> 03:10.055
She hauled off.

03:10.057 --> 03:12.325
Shot him
in the head.

03:12.393 --> 03:13.392
Jesus.

03:13.460 --> 03:15.460
Pope had to drag her
out of there,

03:15.530 --> 03:16.729
left his truck.

03:16.797 --> 03:19.131
And you're just
telling me this now?

03:19.200 --> 03:23.068
Pope's cousins have been
calling Smurf's phone, okay?

03:23.070 --> 03:25.004
They know
we live in Oceanside.

03:27.141 --> 03:28.674
Man:
<i> Good morning, Oceanside.</i>

03:28.676 --> 03:31.076
<i> We have some three-</i>
<i> to five-foot-plus waves</i>

03:31.078 --> 03:33.078
<i> coming in today,</i>
<i> some overhead swells</i>

03:33.080 --> 03:34.747
<i> that are up</i>
<i> a little bit from yesterday.</i>

03:34.815 --> 03:39.218
♪♪

03:39.286 --> 03:41.554
<i> Primary spout...</i>

03:41.622 --> 03:43.356
<i> Secondary...</i>

03:43.424 --> 03:52.164
♪♪

03:52.233 --> 03:53.933
Jesus.

03:58.573 --> 04:00.505
J: Anything?

04:00.507 --> 04:03.442
No.
They call again?

04:03.510 --> 04:04.643
Yeah.

04:04.712 --> 04:14.653
♪♪

04:14.722 --> 04:19.124
♪♪

04:19.126 --> 04:21.060
What time
does the mail place open?

04:21.128 --> 04:22.527
9:00.

04:22.529 --> 04:27.400
♪♪

04:27.468 --> 04:29.868
We need to get this
out of the house,

04:29.937 --> 04:31.336
keep it stashed
as leverage.

04:31.338 --> 04:33.538
You see anything
on your way in?

04:33.608 --> 04:35.274
No.

04:35.342 --> 04:36.809
What's the plan?

04:36.878 --> 04:41.180
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

04:46.353 --> 04:48.087
We give it back.

04:48.890 --> 04:50.155
[ Scoffs ]

04:50.224 --> 04:53.292
This is
a million dollars.

04:53.360 --> 04:54.927
In gold.

04:57.698 --> 04:59.799
Yeah,
Pope's right.

05:00.901 --> 05:02.034
Seriously?

05:02.103 --> 05:03.636
With the
kind of firepower

05:03.704 --> 05:05.104
up on that
Prepper compound,

05:05.172 --> 05:07.640
you think
we can all go up against that?

05:07.708 --> 05:08.974
Okay, fine.

05:09.043 --> 05:10.843
Well,
then we take off

05:10.912 --> 05:12.377
and just wait
for it to blow over.

05:12.379 --> 05:14.980
Smurf killed their father,
and we stole their gold.

05:15.049 --> 05:17.149
This is never gonna blow over,
Craig.

05:18.385 --> 05:21.320
The only way to keep this gold
is to kill them all.

05:22.589 --> 05:24.323
We're not doing that.

05:26.327 --> 05:28.261
They're my cousins.

05:28.329 --> 05:29.594
You just met them.

05:29.596 --> 05:31.864
They're blood.

05:31.932 --> 05:35.400
We're giving it back.

05:35.402 --> 05:37.470
This is all Smurf.

05:38.673 --> 05:40.005
♪♪

05:40.007 --> 05:42.941
♪<i> I need a small vacation</i> ♪

05:43.010 --> 05:46.812
♪<i> But it don't look like rain</i> ♪

05:46.814 --> 05:47.880
Hey, watch it, kid!

05:47.949 --> 05:49.148
Don't touch me!

05:49.216 --> 05:51.016
I didn't touch you.
You pushed me!

05:51.085 --> 05:53.819
I didn't do any --
Mommy!

05:53.821 --> 05:56.489
Hey!
Leave her alone.

05:56.557 --> 06:04.096
♪<i> And I need you</i>
<i> more than want you</i> ♪

06:04.165 --> 06:09.835
♪<i> And I want you for all time</i> ♪

06:09.837 --> 06:12.104
♪<i> And the Wichita lineman</i> ♪

06:12.173 --> 06:13.506
Hey.

06:13.574 --> 06:14.974
This ain't a library.

06:15.042 --> 06:16.041
Oh, it's not?

06:16.110 --> 06:17.643
You gonna
buy that or what?

06:17.712 --> 06:22.447
♪<i> Is still on the line</i> ♪
No, no. Sorry.

06:22.517 --> 06:26.519
♪♪

06:26.587 --> 06:28.387
You have a good day.

06:28.455 --> 06:32.658
♪♪

06:32.727 --> 06:34.727
Andrew.
Come on.

06:34.795 --> 06:40.866
♪♪

06:40.868 --> 06:42.467
Damn, kids.

06:42.469 --> 06:45.538
♪♪

06:45.606 --> 06:47.540
Okay.

06:47.608 --> 06:48.941
♪♪

06:49.010 --> 06:50.609
Let me have it,
baby.

06:50.678 --> 06:52.878
♪<i> When I looked</i>
<i> out the window</i> ♪

06:52.880 --> 06:54.947
♪<i> On the hardship</i>
<i> that had struck</i> ♪
So, what are we thinking?

06:55.016 --> 06:56.749
♪<i> I saw seven phials open</i> ♪

06:56.817 --> 06:59.484
♪<i> The plague</i>
<i> claimed man and son</i> ♪
$80?

06:59.554 --> 07:01.020
$100?

07:01.088 --> 07:02.421
That only happened
one time.

07:02.489 --> 07:05.824
It just means that
it can happen again.

07:05.893 --> 07:07.492
You know,
before you guys were born,

07:07.562 --> 07:10.095
I got one with
a lottery ticket in it.

07:10.164 --> 07:13.566
Well, you know what I got
for that lottery ticket?

07:13.634 --> 07:15.968
$50!

07:16.037 --> 07:17.970
That was with Daddy,
right?

07:18.039 --> 07:20.906
♪<i> Come on down</i> ♪

07:20.908 --> 07:21.840
♪<i> Come on down</i> ♪

07:21.909 --> 07:23.709
♪<i> We'll make the stand</i> ♪

07:23.778 --> 07:26.045
Yeah, baby.

07:26.113 --> 07:27.780
Forgot.

07:27.848 --> 07:30.115
♪♪

07:30.184 --> 07:32.185
♪ Bum-ba-da-dum ba-dum

07:32.253 --> 07:34.319
Can we go someplace
with a pool?!

07:34.389 --> 07:35.320
Yes, we can!

07:35.390 --> 07:36.521
Yes!

07:36.591 --> 07:38.057
What about you, baby?
You want to swim, too?

07:38.125 --> 07:40.259
♪<i> Don't say I didn't warn you</i> ♪

07:40.327 --> 07:41.460
♪<i> This prophecy's coming true</i> ♪

07:41.528 --> 07:42.795
Hey, monkey.

07:42.864 --> 07:44.063
♪<i> The cavalry is thundering</i> ♪

07:44.131 --> 07:46.865
Do you want to get...

07:46.934 --> 07:48.867
burgers for dinner?

07:48.936 --> 07:51.536
♪<i> Come on down</i>
<i> and meet your maker</i> ♪

07:51.606 --> 07:54.339
Could I get
a kids' meal?
Yes.

07:54.409 --> 07:56.541
♪<i> Come on down</i>
<i> and make the stand</i> ♪
Yes!

07:56.543 --> 07:58.543
♪<i> Come on down</i> ♪
[ Barking ]

07:58.545 --> 08:00.145
♪<i> Come on down</i> ♪
[ Howls ]

08:00.147 --> 08:01.680
♪<i> Come on</i> ♪
[ All barking, howling ]

08:01.749 --> 08:03.816
♪<i> And we'll make the stand</i> ♪
[ Engine starts ]

08:03.884 --> 08:06.351
♪<i> Come on down</i>
<i> and meet your maker</i> ♪

08:06.353 --> 08:10.022
♪<i> Come on down</i>
<i> and make the stand</i> ♪

08:10.091 --> 08:13.225
This really
the best plan?

08:13.294 --> 08:14.760
Yeah.

08:14.829 --> 08:16.762
This?

08:16.831 --> 08:18.431
Truck I left
at the compound

08:18.499 --> 08:20.766
is registered
to this place.

08:20.768 --> 08:23.970
It's all they have
besides Smurf's phone number.

08:26.107 --> 08:28.341
Just feels lame
sitting around.

08:32.647 --> 08:34.847
You know Smurf wanted us
to have that gold.

08:34.916 --> 08:36.582
Smurf didn't go there
for the gold.

08:36.651 --> 08:39.051
Look, I'm just saying
if we have the gold,

08:39.120 --> 08:40.953
that we should
just use it.

08:50.197 --> 08:52.365
Place should be
open by now.

09:02.743 --> 09:12.685
♪♪

09:12.753 --> 09:22.695
♪♪

09:22.763 --> 09:24.897
♪♪

09:24.966 --> 09:26.832
Alright.

09:26.834 --> 09:36.641
♪♪

09:36.643 --> 09:37.642
♪♪

09:37.644 --> 09:41.446
Whoa.

09:41.448 --> 09:43.516
Shit.

09:48.923 --> 09:50.790
[ Groans ]

09:54.195 --> 09:57.196
Pope:
How many were there?

09:57.264 --> 09:58.998
Four.

09:59.066 --> 10:01.400
Waiting for me.

10:01.468 --> 10:03.468
Y-You guys know
I got you, right?

10:03.538 --> 10:05.004
Always.

10:05.072 --> 10:06.672
But they were packing.

10:06.741 --> 10:08.273
Big-ass guns.

10:08.275 --> 10:10.743
I thought
I was dead.

10:10.811 --> 10:12.678
What did they want?

10:12.747 --> 10:15.014
♪♪

10:15.082 --> 10:17.282
Mail out of the box,

10:17.284 --> 10:20.819
plus the address
we had on file.

10:20.888 --> 10:22.154
The address
to our house?

10:22.223 --> 10:24.623
No,
the other place.

10:24.692 --> 10:26.759
The -- The apartment.

10:26.827 --> 10:28.627
Whoa,
what apartment?

10:28.696 --> 10:30.429
♪♪

10:30.497 --> 10:31.430
For Smurf.

10:31.498 --> 10:33.632
Pope: What are you
talking about?

10:33.701 --> 10:35.368
It's right here.

10:35.436 --> 10:42.375
♪♪

10:42.443 --> 10:45.110
3435 the Strand,
Apartment 3D.

10:45.179 --> 10:47.112
What the hell is that?

10:47.181 --> 10:48.447
3435?

10:48.515 --> 10:49.382
Do you know it?

10:49.450 --> 10:51.384
No, I don't.

10:51.452 --> 10:53.518
Let's go there.

10:53.520 --> 10:55.188
Let's go.

10:55.256 --> 10:57.456
Get yourself
to urgent care, man.

10:57.524 --> 11:07.466
♪♪

11:07.534 --> 11:13.939
♪♪

11:13.941 --> 11:15.274
That's the last of it,
yeah?

11:15.342 --> 11:17.443
Yeah.

11:22.417 --> 11:25.484
I can't believe we're still
doing Smurf's shit.

11:27.021 --> 11:34.293
♪♪

11:34.361 --> 11:36.695
Smurf said
Adrian was talking to the cops.

11:36.764 --> 11:41.566
♪♪

11:41.568 --> 11:44.369
She told you that?

11:44.439 --> 11:45.771
Yeah.

11:45.773 --> 11:47.706
And...?

11:47.775 --> 11:49.241
♪♪

11:49.310 --> 11:52.044
I'm wondering if there's
anything we need to do about it.

11:52.113 --> 11:56.048
♪♪

11:56.117 --> 11:58.317
"Anything we need
to do about it."

11:58.385 --> 12:01.320
♪♪

12:01.388 --> 12:03.856
I handled it.

12:03.924 --> 12:05.858
How?

12:05.926 --> 12:08.861
♪♪

12:08.929 --> 12:10.796
It's handled.

12:10.798 --> 12:16.469
♪♪

12:16.537 --> 12:18.471
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:18.539 --> 12:21.474
♪♪

12:21.542 --> 12:23.208
Shit.

12:23.210 --> 12:25.144
The cousins
are in Oceanside.

12:25.212 --> 12:33.686
♪♪

12:33.754 --> 12:40.493
♪<i> Sucker punch is</i>
<i> in your heart</i> ♪

12:40.561 --> 12:47.833
♪<i> Life is reason,</i>
<i> light is clue</i> ♪

12:47.902 --> 12:51.971
♪<i> My shape is shapeless</i>
<i> in your suit</i> ♪

12:52.039 --> 12:52.972
Perfect.

12:53.040 --> 12:57.242
♪♪

12:57.244 --> 12:59.111
How's that different
than a cigarette?

12:59.180 --> 13:00.513
It's just different.

13:00.581 --> 13:02.647
But how?

13:02.649 --> 13:04.649
Why don't you swim?

13:04.651 --> 13:06.185
♪♪

13:06.253 --> 13:10.455
♪<i> A simple sun</i>
<i> is slowly sinking</i> ♪

13:10.525 --> 13:12.791
♪<i> Roman shoes and pretty hats</i> ♪

13:12.860 --> 13:15.794
They're curious
at that age.

13:15.863 --> 13:16.729
Yeah.

13:16.797 --> 13:19.932
♪♪

13:20.001 --> 13:22.601
♪<i> Glitter bombs</i>
<i> that beat the beat</i> ♪

13:22.670 --> 13:27.873
♪♪

13:27.942 --> 13:34.279
♪<i> You comb the night</i>
<i> 'cause you're a cruiser</i> ♪

13:34.281 --> 13:38.083
♪<i> And ya --</i>
<i> ya never get enough</i> ♪
Hey. Come here.

13:38.085 --> 13:41.153
Will you help me?

13:41.222 --> 13:42.487
Thank you.

13:42.489 --> 13:43.822
♪<i> And takin' off the heat</i> ♪

13:43.891 --> 13:47.426
♪<i> When you're on</i>
<i> the moonlight run</i> ♪

13:47.494 --> 13:54.967
♪♪

13:55.036 --> 13:55.968
Julia: Stop!

13:56.037 --> 13:58.837
Don't do that!
I told you stop!

13:58.906 --> 14:00.706
Don't! Don't!

14:00.708 --> 14:03.108
Is that your kid?

14:03.110 --> 14:05.644
Come on!
Yeah.

14:05.713 --> 14:07.180
Please, stop!

14:07.248 --> 14:09.181
They're just playing.

14:09.250 --> 14:13.786
♪♪

14:13.855 --> 14:15.588
Stop!

14:15.656 --> 14:18.191
I told you stop!

14:18.259 --> 14:20.459
Don't do that!

14:20.527 --> 14:23.195
♪♪

14:23.264 --> 14:25.130
Stop! Stop!

14:25.132 --> 14:28.467
♪♪

14:28.535 --> 14:31.536
Hey!
Will you stop him?

14:31.606 --> 14:33.205
They're just playing,
right?

14:33.274 --> 14:35.274
♪♪

14:35.342 --> 14:36.809
Man:
Hey, cut it out, guys!

14:36.878 --> 14:38.210
Hey, knock it off!
Hey!

14:38.279 --> 14:39.678
Will you
get him off my son?!

14:39.747 --> 14:41.614
♪♪

14:41.682 --> 14:43.749
Julia: Andrew,
don't do that!

14:43.751 --> 14:44.817
Stop! Stop!

14:44.886 --> 14:46.085
Andrew!
Let go!

14:46.153 --> 14:47.420
Break it up!
Let him go!

14:47.488 --> 14:49.288
Let go!
Off!

14:49.356 --> 14:51.357
Andrew.
Man: Let go!

14:53.828 --> 14:59.564
[ Coughing ]

14:59.566 --> 15:03.903
You okay, buddy?
You okay?

15:03.971 --> 15:07.239
[ Coughing continues ]

15:07.308 --> 15:09.174
What is wrong
with you?!

15:09.176 --> 15:11.576
I'm calling the cops
on you.

15:11.578 --> 15:13.913
And your little freak!
Do you hear me?

15:13.981 --> 15:15.748
Do you?!

15:18.253 --> 15:20.319
Pack it up.

15:28.463 --> 15:30.529
What's up?
What are we doing here?

15:30.598 --> 15:33.666
Turns out that Smurf owns
one of the apartments up there.

15:42.076 --> 15:44.076
You know about this,
J?

15:44.145 --> 15:45.745
No.

15:53.020 --> 15:55.220
♪♪

15:55.222 --> 15:58.023
Come on.
Over here.

15:58.025 --> 15:59.892
Who's that out front?

15:59.961 --> 16:01.160
That's Odin.

16:01.228 --> 16:03.228
Where's the rest of them?

16:03.298 --> 16:05.364
Up in the apartment.

16:05.432 --> 16:07.900
One of them just had a smoke
up on the balcony.

16:07.969 --> 16:10.569
Left the sliding door
open.

16:10.637 --> 16:12.171
How do you want
to do this?

16:12.239 --> 16:17.776
♪♪

16:17.845 --> 16:18.911
You got a $20?

16:18.980 --> 16:20.245
I got a $5.

16:20.315 --> 16:22.647
Yeah,
that'll work.

16:22.649 --> 16:25.518
You gotta think,
with all this shit here,

16:25.586 --> 16:27.186
she's probably
still in town.

16:27.254 --> 16:29.922
♪♪

16:29.991 --> 16:32.591
No food!

16:32.660 --> 16:34.327
Nothing!

16:34.395 --> 16:44.337
♪♪

16:44.405 --> 16:54.347
♪♪

16:54.415 --> 17:03.756
♪♪

17:03.824 --> 17:04.757
♪♪

17:04.825 --> 17:06.692
Hey!

17:06.694 --> 17:08.694
What's the matter
with you?!

17:08.696 --> 17:10.495
Piece of shit.
You piece of shit.

17:10.565 --> 17:12.899
Get outta here.
Get outta here.

17:18.639 --> 17:20.606
What's up,
cuz?

17:22.777 --> 17:28.047
♪♪

17:28.115 --> 17:29.848
Yo! Hey!

17:29.917 --> 17:31.784
Got something!

17:31.852 --> 17:34.119
♪♪

17:34.121 --> 17:36.255
Alright.

17:36.323 --> 17:46.199
♪♪

17:46.267 --> 17:48.067
Goddamn it, man.

17:48.135 --> 17:49.935
Five different passports.

17:49.937 --> 17:51.937
This bitch
could be anywhere.

17:51.939 --> 17:55.274
♪♪

17:55.342 --> 17:58.010
Look at that.

17:58.079 --> 18:01.680
That's him, right?

18:01.749 --> 18:03.015
Yeah.

18:03.084 --> 18:04.683
Go!

18:04.752 --> 18:10.489
♪♪

18:10.557 --> 18:13.225
Hey. Jackpot.

18:13.294 --> 18:15.360
Hey, Dave,
get the tools.

18:15.362 --> 18:25.037
♪♪

18:25.106 --> 18:26.505
♪♪

18:26.574 --> 18:28.707
Man: Hide.
Go, go, go, go,
go, go, go!

18:28.776 --> 18:38.517
♪♪

18:38.585 --> 18:41.386
Odin: Mikey.

18:41.388 --> 18:43.188
Yo!

18:43.257 --> 18:45.524
Hey, man, I told you to stay
with the truck.

18:45.593 --> 18:47.392
I need
to take a piss.

18:47.394 --> 18:52.465
♪♪

18:52.533 --> 18:54.467
I told you not to drink
all that Gatorade.

18:54.535 --> 18:55.734
Come on, let me in.

18:55.803 --> 18:57.470
You can watch the damn truck
from the window.

18:57.538 --> 18:58.804
Doesn't feel right,
man.

18:58.806 --> 18:59.872
Don't open that door,
Mikey.

18:59.941 --> 19:02.141
Come on, man. Just --
Don't do it.

19:02.209 --> 19:05.144
♪♪

19:05.212 --> 19:06.745
Mikey!

19:06.814 --> 19:09.148
Get back down there and
let us know if anyone's coming.

19:09.216 --> 19:12.485
♪♪

19:12.553 --> 19:14.687
Morning, fellas.

19:17.191 --> 19:18.457
Put your guns down!
Put 'em down!

19:18.526 --> 19:22.862
Keep your eyes on them!
You hear me?

19:22.930 --> 19:24.796
Odin,
are you alone?

19:24.798 --> 19:26.798
What do you think,
dipshit?

19:26.800 --> 19:28.133
Tell him
we want to talk.

19:28.202 --> 19:31.203
Says they want to talk.

19:31.272 --> 19:34.340
Yeah, listen,
everybody be cool, okay?

19:34.408 --> 19:37.543
Just relax.
I'm gonna open the door.

19:37.611 --> 19:39.679
Odin: Alright.
Very slowly, alright?

19:39.747 --> 19:42.814
♪♪

19:42.816 --> 19:44.350
Stay back.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:44.418 --> 19:45.817
Stay back!

19:45.819 --> 19:47.086
Move in slowly!

19:47.154 --> 19:48.888
We're backing up.
Get in.

19:48.956 --> 19:50.155
Come on, come on, come on.
Get in.

19:50.224 --> 19:51.423
Alright.
Now, shut up.

19:51.425 --> 19:52.692
Shut up.
Odin: Take it easy.

19:52.760 --> 19:54.226
Shut up!
Take it easy.

19:54.228 --> 19:56.428
Don't tell me to --
Shut up!
Take it --

19:56.430 --> 19:57.897
So, where's your bitch
of a mother?

19:57.965 --> 19:59.365
Shut the hell up,
man!

19:59.433 --> 20:02.034
Where the hell
is she?!

20:02.103 --> 20:03.302
You said
you wanted to talk.

20:03.371 --> 20:05.104
So, talk.
What is it?

20:05.172 --> 20:06.906
We're gonna give you
your gold back.

20:06.974 --> 20:08.107
Just like that?

20:08.175 --> 20:10.309
We give you
your gold back.

20:10.378 --> 20:13.779
You leave town.
And we're done.

20:13.847 --> 20:15.314
Our father is dead!

20:15.383 --> 20:17.383
Where the hell
is your mother?

20:17.451 --> 20:20.519
[ Door opens ]
I shot her.

20:20.588 --> 20:21.653
And who are you?

20:21.723 --> 20:23.655
I'm her grandson.

20:23.657 --> 20:25.190
She had cancer.

20:25.259 --> 20:27.126
She wanted to die.

20:29.130 --> 20:31.063
I don't believe
any of you.

20:31.132 --> 20:32.864
I want to see
a body.

20:32.866 --> 20:35.000
There is no body.

20:35.069 --> 20:37.269
We cremated her.

20:37.271 --> 20:38.870
And we want to give you
back the gold.

20:38.872 --> 20:41.073
So enough of the bullshit
already.

20:41.142 --> 20:44.076
It was just
a job that went bad.

20:44.145 --> 20:47.279
We did not know
Smurf was gonna shoot your dad.

20:47.348 --> 20:49.014
She was settling
old scores.

20:49.083 --> 20:51.884
It wasn't about you.
It wasn't about us.

20:51.953 --> 20:54.686
Whatever happened
between your father

20:54.688 --> 20:56.455
and our mother
is done.

21:02.296 --> 21:03.695
Alright,
I'm putting it down.

21:03.697 --> 21:05.564
What are you doing?
What are you doing, man?

21:05.633 --> 21:07.366
I'm putting
the weapon down.
Come on.

21:07.435 --> 21:09.835
Aw, come on, man.
This is bullshit.
Hey, Jeremy.

21:09.904 --> 21:11.303
We came
for the gold.

21:11.372 --> 21:13.572
We came for the gold,
right?

21:13.641 --> 21:16.308
♪♪

21:16.377 --> 21:17.643
Right?

21:17.711 --> 21:19.311
Right.

21:19.380 --> 21:22.381
♪♪

21:22.450 --> 21:23.182
Where is it?

21:23.251 --> 21:24.784
It's in
a storage unit nearby.

21:24.852 --> 21:26.652
We'll get it,
and we'll bring it back.

21:26.720 --> 21:28.187
Yeah.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

21:28.255 --> 21:29.789
I'll go.
I'll go.

21:29.857 --> 21:31.723
This is better.

21:31.725 --> 21:33.993
♪♪

21:34.061 --> 21:35.194
Everything's good.

21:35.262 --> 21:36.862
Just be cool,
alright?

21:36.931 --> 21:39.865
♪♪

21:39.934 --> 21:41.267
Are the police
really coming?

21:41.335 --> 21:43.135
Of course not,
baby.

21:43.137 --> 21:45.104
Then why
do we have to leave?

21:47.875 --> 21:50.409
'Cause you never wait around
for trouble,

21:50.478 --> 21:52.612
even if you don't think
it's gonna happen.

21:52.680 --> 21:54.514
Right, Andrew?

22:00.888 --> 22:03.089
Why is everybody
looking at us?

22:04.892 --> 22:06.959
'Cause we're special.

22:14.502 --> 22:16.636
Man:
Um, they're pretty good.

22:22.844 --> 22:32.451
♪♪

22:32.520 --> 22:37.523
♪♪

22:37.591 --> 22:39.791
So, what kind of name
is Smurf?

22:39.861 --> 22:41.994
David:
It's a cartoon, right?

22:41.996 --> 22:43.128
With blue midgets?

22:43.197 --> 22:44.596
[ Laughs ]

22:44.598 --> 22:46.398
And you all
called her that?

22:46.467 --> 22:51.470
♪♪

22:51.539 --> 22:52.471
Who's that?

22:52.540 --> 22:54.806
This is Mom.

22:54.808 --> 22:58.477
So, you shoot their mother,
and you're still breathing?

22:58.546 --> 23:08.354
♪♪

23:08.422 --> 23:11.557
♪♪

23:11.625 --> 23:13.359
They're back.

23:20.301 --> 23:21.633
You know,
your dad's buried

23:21.635 --> 23:24.504
in a field
near our house, right?

23:27.308 --> 23:29.375
Yeah.

23:29.443 --> 23:32.512
My old man
used to tell us about him.

23:32.580 --> 23:33.845
I never met him.

23:33.847 --> 23:36.115
He was dead before
I was even born, but...

23:42.456 --> 23:45.257
I don't know, maybe you should
come by sometime,

23:45.326 --> 23:47.260
pay your respects.

23:59.006 --> 24:01.541
You got it?

24:01.609 --> 24:02.942
Like,
all of it?

24:03.010 --> 24:04.644
Let's go.
Get in the car.

24:06.213 --> 24:09.382
[ Door opens ]

24:12.353 --> 24:14.820
[ Doors closing ]

24:14.888 --> 24:17.223
[ Engine starts ]

24:23.297 --> 24:25.231
So,
that's it?

24:26.968 --> 24:28.901
It's done.

24:28.970 --> 24:30.903
♪♪

24:30.972 --> 24:33.505
Alright.

24:33.574 --> 24:43.115
♪♪

24:43.117 --> 24:44.784
Mmm.

24:44.852 --> 24:46.919
♪♪

24:46.988 --> 24:49.321
Mmm.

24:49.390 --> 24:51.590
Yeah, Smurf knew
how to make good lasagna.

24:51.659 --> 24:53.392
Mmm.

24:53.461 --> 24:57.597
You think she wrote
the recipes down?

24:57.665 --> 24:59.665
Why?
You want to start cooking?

24:59.733 --> 25:02.201
I don't know, I just thought
Nick might want to know

25:02.269 --> 25:03.803
how his grandma's
lasagna tastes.

25:03.871 --> 25:06.872
♪♪

25:06.941 --> 25:09.008
His grandma?

25:09.076 --> 25:19.151
♪♪

25:19.153 --> 25:29.161
♪♪

25:29.163 --> 25:38.570
♪♪

25:38.640 --> 25:40.372
♪♪

25:40.441 --> 25:42.774
What do you want to do
about her ashes?

25:42.776 --> 25:44.576
She bought us
those burial plots

25:44.578 --> 25:46.979
where she moved Julia.

25:47.048 --> 25:49.581
Probably wants
to be there.

25:49.583 --> 25:52.384
Aren't you supposed to put
the whole body in cemeteries?

25:52.386 --> 25:55.321
You can bury ashes
in a cemetery, too, bud.

25:55.389 --> 25:57.523
It just seems...

25:57.591 --> 25:59.358
kind of boring
for Smurf.

26:01.462 --> 26:03.395
Terry McGillis rolled up
his dad's ashes

26:03.397 --> 26:04.997
into a fatty
and smoked him.

26:05.066 --> 26:06.065
That's bullshit.

26:06.133 --> 26:07.533
True story.

26:07.601 --> 26:09.368
Said he started
hallucinating and shit.

26:17.144 --> 26:18.344
[ Door closes ]

26:21.282 --> 26:23.082
What's that?

26:23.150 --> 26:25.251
Your copies of
Smurf's will.

26:30.024 --> 26:32.491
Where'd you get these?

26:32.560 --> 26:35.294
Angela signed for them
when they were delivered.

26:35.363 --> 26:36.629
She gave them
to me.

26:38.900 --> 26:40.900
You just opened them?

26:40.968 --> 26:42.635
No, she did.

26:46.908 --> 26:49.375
Pope know about this?

26:49.443 --> 26:52.912
Yeah,
I told him.

26:52.980 --> 26:54.380
You should read it.

26:54.448 --> 27:04.123
♪♪

27:04.192 --> 27:14.133
♪♪

27:14.202 --> 27:24.143
♪♪

27:24.212 --> 27:30.015
♪♪

27:30.084 --> 27:32.017
[ Keypad beeping ]

27:32.086 --> 27:42.027
♪♪

27:42.096 --> 27:52.037
♪♪

27:52.106 --> 28:00.546
♪♪

28:03.050 --> 28:05.251
Julia: Mommy,
are we going?

28:14.061 --> 28:16.596
Watch! Aah!
[ Laughs ]

28:22.670 --> 28:25.737
Hey, Andrew,
give me your shirt.

28:25.807 --> 28:27.540
Andrew.

28:28.876 --> 28:38.818
♪♪

28:38.886 --> 28:47.893
♪♪

28:47.962 --> 28:49.629
Wait in the car.

28:49.697 --> 28:59.505
♪♪

28:59.573 --> 29:09.515
♪♪

29:09.583 --> 29:19.525
♪♪

29:19.593 --> 29:29.335
♪♪

29:29.403 --> 29:30.736
♪♪

29:30.804 --> 29:32.137
[ Indistinct shouting,
woman screams ]

29:32.206 --> 29:35.875
Man: Oh, geez!
Oh! Help!

29:35.943 --> 29:37.877
♪♪

29:40.281 --> 29:42.414
What the hell is this?

29:42.416 --> 29:43.615
Who the hell
is Pamela Johnson?

29:43.685 --> 29:45.417
Yeah, I know.
Right?

29:45.419 --> 29:46.886
She's one of
Smurf's old pals.

29:46.954 --> 29:49.388
The will says she gets
almost everything.

29:57.164 --> 29:59.098
I'll check the breaker.

29:59.166 --> 30:01.100
[ Scoffs ]

30:01.168 --> 30:02.502
[ Tires screech ]

30:02.570 --> 30:06.505
[ Engine revs ]

30:06.574 --> 30:09.975
[ Tires screech ]

30:10.044 --> 30:11.611
Shit.

30:22.189 --> 30:25.257
[ Gunshots ]

30:25.326 --> 30:28.193
Move!

30:28.262 --> 30:29.829
Aah!

30:32.400 --> 30:35.067
[ Gunshots ]

30:35.136 --> 30:36.135
Gah!

30:36.203 --> 30:38.337
They got night vision.

30:38.406 --> 30:40.206
Odin, perimeter.

30:40.274 --> 30:41.607
Mike,
take the back.

30:41.675 --> 30:43.509
Dave,
you're with me.

30:51.553 --> 30:53.485
Deran:
You alright?

30:53.554 --> 30:55.688
Yeah.
Got shit in my eye.

32:50.004 --> 32:51.537
[ Gunshots ]

32:51.605 --> 32:53.940
[ Grunting ]

32:55.009 --> 32:56.676
[ Gunshots ]

32:58.812 --> 33:01.047
[ Both grunting ]

33:02.350 --> 33:03.683
[ Grunts ]

33:04.752 --> 33:06.619
[ Gun cocks ]

33:09.757 --> 33:11.223
[ Gunshots, glass shattering ]

33:11.225 --> 33:12.592
Aah!

33:14.362 --> 33:15.695
[ Groans ]

33:22.436 --> 33:24.604
[ Grunts ]

33:32.714 --> 33:34.714
[ Grunts ]

33:34.782 --> 33:37.016
[ Groans ]

33:54.135 --> 33:55.868
Davy!

34:07.415 --> 34:10.116
[ Groaning ]

34:12.486 --> 34:14.587
I'm alright.
It's just my shoulder.

34:16.290 --> 34:17.289
[ Gasps ]

34:17.291 --> 34:18.724
[ Groans ]

34:38.446 --> 34:39.779
[ Both grunting ]

34:39.847 --> 34:41.713
Goddamn it!

34:41.715 --> 34:44.784
[ Grunting ]

35:27.294 --> 35:29.795
[ Panting ]

35:43.878 --> 35:50.549
♪♪

35:50.618 --> 35:51.950
[ Groans, coughs ]

35:52.020 --> 35:55.421
Ohh, yo.
He's alive, man.

35:55.489 --> 35:56.555
Just go.
Bro.

35:56.624 --> 35:58.490
Keep moving.
Just go.

35:58.559 --> 36:00.559
[ Both grunt ]

36:00.561 --> 36:03.562
Aah! [ Sighs ]

36:03.631 --> 36:07.566
♪♪

36:07.635 --> 36:11.037
[ Groans ]

36:11.105 --> 36:12.905
Aah! Ha!

36:12.973 --> 36:14.172
Pope: Sirens.

36:14.242 --> 36:15.374
Deran's gonna have to deal
with the cops.

36:15.443 --> 36:16.909
Let's go.

36:16.977 --> 36:18.711
♪♪

36:18.779 --> 36:20.178
Aaaaah!

36:20.248 --> 36:21.580
[ Groans ]

36:21.649 --> 36:24.050
♪♪

36:24.118 --> 36:25.984
Keep going.
Keep going.

36:25.986 --> 36:27.185
[ Siren wails ]

36:27.255 --> 36:36.262
♪♪

36:36.330 --> 36:37.263
♪♪

36:37.331 --> 36:39.665
[ Siren wails ]

36:39.734 --> 36:46.605
♪♪

36:46.674 --> 36:48.674
Hands.
Whoa.

36:48.743 --> 36:49.942
♪♪

36:50.010 --> 36:51.877
You guys here
about the lights?

36:51.946 --> 36:54.212
No.
Oh.

36:54.282 --> 36:56.682
Any idea when we're gonna
get power back on?

36:56.751 --> 36:59.752
A few
of your neighbors called.

36:59.820 --> 37:02.088
Said they heard gunshots.

37:02.156 --> 37:04.957
Yeah, we were playing
this shooting game.

37:05.025 --> 37:06.492
Had the volume up really loud.

37:06.560 --> 37:08.026
These neighbors complain
about it all the time, so...

37:08.028 --> 37:10.362
You were playing
in the dark?

37:10.431 --> 37:11.697
No,
this just happened.

37:11.766 --> 37:13.900
What happened
to your gate here?

37:13.968 --> 37:16.569
That was a drunk driver
a couple of days ago.

37:16.637 --> 37:18.637
♪♪

37:18.706 --> 37:20.572
Alright, so, we're gonna need
to check it out, okay?

37:20.641 --> 37:23.576
You got a warrant?

37:23.644 --> 37:26.044
We have probable cause
with the gunshots, yeah.

37:26.046 --> 37:28.114
Oh, I told you
we were playing video games.

37:28.182 --> 37:30.516
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

37:30.585 --> 37:34.320
♪♪

37:34.388 --> 37:36.522
Go call it in.

37:36.591 --> 37:38.457
647.

37:38.459 --> 37:40.592
Tell the others
to stand down.

37:40.661 --> 37:42.328
Go on.

37:42.396 --> 37:48.935
♪♪

37:49.003 --> 37:50.669
647.
Stand down.

37:50.738 --> 37:52.538
All units, down.
647.

37:55.143 --> 37:57.075
You're lucky
I got here first.

37:57.145 --> 37:59.345
There's three more cars
behind that one.

37:59.413 --> 38:04.683
♪♪

38:04.752 --> 38:06.685
Give me a minute.
Yeah.

38:06.754 --> 38:16.695
♪♪

38:16.764 --> 38:26.104
♪♪

38:26.174 --> 38:28.106
Pope:
Are we good?

38:28.176 --> 38:29.708
Yeah, man, we're great.

38:29.777 --> 38:30.909
I'll see you there.
Yeah.

38:30.911 --> 38:40.586
♪♪

38:40.655 --> 38:44.657
This shit never happened
when Smurf was alive.

38:44.725 --> 38:46.425
Better tighten up.

38:50.398 --> 38:52.398
Let's go.

38:53.534 --> 38:55.401
[ Engine starts ]

38:55.469 --> 39:02.741
♪♪

39:02.810 --> 39:05.544
[ Brakes squeal ]

39:05.546 --> 39:07.746
♪♪

39:07.815 --> 39:08.747
[ Groans ]

39:08.816 --> 39:10.416
[ Grunts ]

39:10.484 --> 39:17.823
♪♪

39:17.892 --> 39:21.560
[ Muffled speaking ]

39:21.562 --> 39:30.436
♪♪

39:30.504 --> 39:31.437
♪♪

39:31.505 --> 39:32.705
Are we doing this?

39:32.773 --> 39:34.640
Grab his leg.

39:34.709 --> 39:36.642
Now!

39:36.711 --> 39:41.580
♪♪

39:41.649 --> 39:43.449
[ Muffled groaning ]

39:43.517 --> 39:49.055
♪♪

39:49.123 --> 39:52.591
[ Breathing heavily ]

39:52.660 --> 39:54.393
♪♪

39:54.462 --> 39:57.663
I'll meet you
back at the house.

39:57.732 --> 39:59.065
Pope.
You take care
of the truck.

39:59.133 --> 40:00.266
I'll meet you
at the house.

40:00.334 --> 40:01.467
Pope.

40:01.535 --> 40:03.802
I'll meet you
at the house!

40:03.871 --> 40:06.605
What are you
waiting for?!

40:06.674 --> 40:12.611
♪♪

40:12.680 --> 40:15.948
[ Engine starts ]

40:16.016 --> 40:16.949
♪♪

40:17.017 --> 40:20.152
[ Engine starts ]

40:20.220 --> 40:23.222
[ Engine revs ]

40:24.425 --> 40:26.825
♪<i> Take your baby by the hand</i> ♪

40:26.894 --> 40:28.627
♪♪

40:28.696 --> 40:31.297
♪<i> And make her do</i>
<i> a high handstand</i> ♪

40:31.365 --> 40:32.899
♪♪

40:32.967 --> 40:36.168
♪<i> And take your baby</i>
<i> by the heel</i> ♪

40:36.236 --> 40:37.970
♪♪

40:38.038 --> 40:40.839
♪<i> And do the next thing</i>
<i> that you feel</i> ♪

40:40.908 --> 40:42.508
♪♪

40:42.576 --> 40:45.644
♪<i> We were so in phase</i> ♪

40:45.713 --> 40:47.045
♪♪

40:47.115 --> 40:50.649
♪<i> In our dance hall days</i> ♪

40:50.718 --> 40:52.318
♪<i> We were cool</i> ♪

40:52.386 --> 40:54.787
Why do you get it
if you don't want the toy?

40:54.855 --> 40:57.323
♪♪

40:57.391 --> 40:59.458
He likes
to open the box.

40:59.527 --> 41:00.993
♪♪

41:01.061 --> 41:03.395
♪<i> Could believe, do</i> ♪

41:03.464 --> 41:05.397
♪<i> And share in what was true</i> ♪

41:05.466 --> 41:07.199
♪<i> Oh, I said</i> ♪

